Django + React (Full Stack Setup)
If using React as the frontend (often in a subfolder like frontend/) 
.gitignore should include both Django and React-specific ignores.

# === Django Backend ===

# Python
*.py[cod]
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
build/
develop-eggs/
dist/
eggs/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg
pip-log.txt
pip-delete-this-directory.txt

# Django
db.sqlite3
__pycache__/
db.sqlite3
*.log
*.pot
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
*.sqlite3
*.env
.env
.env.*

# Django static/media
/staticfiles/
/media/
/static/
/static_root/
/media_root/

# Migrations
*/migrations/*.py
*/migrations/*.pyc
*/migrations/__pycache__/

# === React Frontend (assumed in a /frontend directory) ===
